-- South African Shares Decline in Opening Trade, Led Lower By Anglo, BHP
-- Gavin Serkin
-- 2010-06-15T07:05:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-15/south-african-shares-decline-in-opening-trade-led-lower-by-anglo-bhp.html

          
          
             South Africa's benchmark stock index,
the FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index, fell 0.44 percent at 9:05
a.m.  
 The index of 164 companies traded on Johannesburg's stock
exchange fell 120.90 to 27,325.19. Among the stocks in the index,
26 rose, 31 fell and 107 were unchanged.  
 Declines in the All Share Index were led by Bhp Billiton,
Anglo American and Sasol.  
          
          


  


        